edu.osu.cse.mmxi.machine.interpreter
Class InstructionParser

java.lang.Object
  edu.osu.cse.mmxi.machine.interpreter.InstructionParser

public class InstructionParser
extends java.lang.Object

InstructionParser turns a 16-bit word into an Instruction that the Interpreter can execute on the Machine.

Instructions are based on the most significant 4 bits in the raw instruction. Since we have exactly 16 instructions, there is no combination of 4 bits which leads to an invalid Instruction. This greatly simplifies the InstructionParser since there is no possibility that the Parser fails to produce an Instruction (though it may not be the instruction intended by the user).

Binary Hex Instruction Name
0000 0x0 BRX Branch NZP
0001 0x1 ADD Addition
0010 0x2 LD Load (Direct Addressing)
0011 0x3 ST Store (Direct Addressing)
0100 0x4 JSR Jump (Page + 9-bit offset)
0101 0x5 AND Bitwise AND
0110 0x6 LDR Load Register
0111 0x7 STR Store Register
1000 0x8 DBUG Debug
1001 0x9 NOT Bitwise Negation
1010 0xA LDI Load (Indirect Addressing)
1011 0xB STI Store (Indirect Addressing)
1100 0xC JSRR Jump (Base Register + 6-bit offset)
1101 0xD RET Return from Subroutine
1110 0xE LEA Load Effective Address
1111 0xF TRAP Trap Vector Call
